This paper deals with the radio network model, which is a common topic in the field of computer networks. The problem of broadcasting messages is a fundamental problem in network communication, which falls under the category of network protocols and algorithms. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of the lower bound on the achievable broadcast throughput, which requires the use of information theory and communication complexity, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves the study of the graph structure and its impact on the broadcast throughput, which falls under the category of graph theory and algorithms, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of the performance limits of the radio network model, which falls under the category of system performance analysis, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
